												<div class="vers-no">17</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Better far, by my way of it, that a man should eat and drink and enjoy the revenues of his own labour, here under the sun, as long as God gives him life; what more can he claim?</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers162623" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">18</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Godâ€™s gift it is, if a man has wealth and goods and freedom to enjoy them, taking what comes to him and profiting by what he has earned.</div>
